This paper proposes a new model for large-scale knowledge graph reasoning, which involves machine learning and natural language processing. The paper discusses the use of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of embeddings and path-based models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) research. Additionally, the paper discusses knowledge base completion tasks, which are related to database systems (cs.DB) and neural networks (cs.NE).
